README file for EVcharge 

This project is a React-based web application for logging electric vehicle (EV) charging sessions. 
It provides a user interface to start, edit and complete a logs of charging sessions, 
and it sends the logged data to a backend server via POST requests in CSV format.

The backend server is expected to be running a CGI script (write_csv.cgi) that accepts 
the CSV data and processes it accordingly. 

This implemewntation distributes the React app as static files (HTML, JS, CSS) 
that can be served by a web server, here busybox running on Termux on an Android device.

The CGI script is expected to be served on the same device, here lighttp listening on port 8090.
(busybox Android version did not seem to be able to handle CGI scripts, but lighttp on Termux did fine.)

The section below of README was generated by the update_evcharge.sh script on 2025-12-04.

